File: Gauteng Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs MEC Lebogang Maile said he is received complaints that some former councillors have been issuing illegal trading permits. TSHWANE - The City of Tshwane may have been placed under administration because of mismanagement. The City has received reports of some councillors acting in ways that are detrimental to the municipality's well being. WATCH: Public engagement on COVID-19 response Gauteng Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs MEC Lebogang Maile said he has received complaints that some former councillors have been issuing illegal trading permits. The country continues to battle the COVID-19 pandemic. He said such acts are criminal and undermine the decision to place the city under administration. The MEC has warned that the municipality will take the strongest possible action against those involved. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs. 